Here's a PlantUML component diagram that captures the static architecture of the ZWT SDK, focusing on the general architectural concern:

```plantuml
@startuml zwt-sdk_zwt

package "ZWT Framework" {
  [Core Abstraction] as core
  [UI Components] as ui
  [Graphics and Input] as graphics
  [Layout Management] as layout
  [Menus] as menus
  [Styling] as styling
  [Backgrounds (Floors)] as floors
  [Utility] as utility
}

package "Platform-Specific Implementations" {
  [Java SE/EE] as se
  [Java ME Embedded] as me
  [Android] as android
}

[Application] as app

core --> ui
core --> graphics
core --> layout
core --> menus
core --> styling
core --> floors
core --> utility

ui --> se
ui --> me
ui --> android

graphics --> se
graphics --> me
graphics --> android

layout --> se
layout --> me
layout --> android

menus --> se
menus --> me
menus --> android

styling --> se
styling --> me
styling --> android

floors --> se
floors --> me
floors --> android

app --> core : uses

@enduml
```